                  </persName>
            . I was in Pitfield-street about two o'clock on the 21st of December, and saw the three prisoners together - they went into an oil-shop, and then to a pawnbroker's; I went in and asked if they had stolen anything, but they had not; I followed them to Mr. Pack's - Platt went in there, and came out with this harness - the other two stood on the opposite side of the way - I followed Platt, and brought him back to Mr. Pack's shop; I then got assistance, and secured the other two.</p>
